<Author>pellegrina_leone
<Content>Nice Location! Hotel Denit is located 2 minutes away from plaza Catalunya, which means it is the centre of Barcelona.It is a brand new with nice style 3 stars hotel.The business room has a good size, a large plasma TV , nice bathroom although there were missing some small details like a brush for the toilet.A good detail was the size of the towels... huge!There is no refrigerator in the room which is not good.The breakfast was poor : toast bread, 3 kind of jam, honey, juice , croissant, coffee and a kind of sweet. That's all!When we asked for an espresso they respond that it was not possible, although in the lobby you can have one.The value for money was really good, 79euro per night including breakfast.In general I believe it will be a good hotel after a while because now Denit has some problems especially with the staff which is unprofessional and they don't have the experience to handle some situations or be flexible , in order the visitors leave the place with a very good impression. 
